animal.description:
***Please DO NOT send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available. If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder- we are still accepting applications for them**

Lulu is in a foster home in Houston TX and can transport mid February to the PNW

Lulu, 4 years old, dachshund, 24 lbs, female. Lulu came to us as an owner surrender. We are hoping to find the best match for this feisty pup. 

Lulu is dog friendly, but when she wants to be done playing she is over it. She is more dominant than submissive. She has met dogs of all sizes and has the same play style. She enjoys chasing other dogs more than she likes playing with them per say. 
Lulu has been around cats and will try to chase them and go after them. We recommend a home with NO cats. 
She needs some training with walking on a leash. If her collar/harness is not secure she will try to wiggle out and run away. She pulls and enjoys sniffing everything around her. 
 She is fully housebroken and sleeps in a kennel with no issues. Occasionally due to the changes from one home to another we have seen some dogs regress. It's possible she may have a few accidents until figuring out the routine in your home. 
Lulu has shown some food aggression so she should be fed separately from other dogs. She loves toys and will hoard them to burry them in her bedding. She does NOT want to share her toys and can become very possessive of her things. 
 She does not have any separation anxiety. However, if left for long periods of time she will find something to get into. 

Lulu first home had younger kids who we think abused her and she is now aggressive towards young children. She has been around 10/12 year olds and has warmed up, but we do not trust she won't snap/bite them. We are recommending a home with no children. 

Lulu loves to cuddle and will sleep at your feet at night. She loves for you to throw the ball--but she won't return it! She is low/moderate energy and would be fine as the only dog in the home where she can be the Queen. 


***Listed BREED and AGE - We are taking our best guess on age, breed and size when fully grown. We rarely know a dog's exact age nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. ***

The first step in our process is filling out an application. We will review your application as soon as we are able- there are two of us and we do the best that we can. We review applications on a first come first serve basis and look for the best fit/match for the dog and applicant.

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/10052

 Hi! My name is Sumatra 
 Welcome all! Come on in. I'm just getting ready to start. Am I showing my best side? I want to be in the movies. I got all prettied up and waited to hear Action but I was told I might make all of the other dogs jealous over my good looks so story time it is...
 I'm guessed to be an Redbone Coonhound Mix and about 2 years young and about 48 lbs. People do tell me that am pretty!
 People also say that I am super sweet and loving and I am happy around people.
 I do have lots of energy as I am still a young dog. So an adopter that is active would be awesome. We could burn off energy together. And a fence yard sounds wonderful too so I can still burn my energy off ....
 I walk on a leash but best to be walked in an area that I can call mine to start till you get to know me and I get to know you ....
 PERK ALERT 
 - very lovable and sweet
- house broken and crate trained
 - knows Come and Sit for the most part ( still working on this.)
 - very playful and good with other dogs my size

 I have to say I have not had a good start in life. So I'm really looking for someone who will give me second chance... I was very skinny when I was rescued. As a result, its left me a bit guarding my things like food, toys and sometimes my people. I think some good training, lots of love, will help turn around things around for me and help me manage my bad habit. Just feeding me in my crate if other dogs are around eating too is an easy way to help me.
 I think I should be in a home with dogs my size because I do like to be in charge and can get excited and not even know my own strength. As for kids, I believe I would be best with older and experienced dog savvy ones....
 So if all of this sounds good to you and you are willing to put in the effort? If so let's do it together and be a happy family 
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description:
PETE is a happy dog. He's active and he likes to talk. He likes other dogs. He is smart. His favorite thing is to have his belly scratched :-)

His adoption fee includes his neutering, vaccines, deworming, microchip. He is a stubby-tail Cattledog/Heeler and was born on a reservation we work with 2018. He has started some obedience training.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Sweet, shy, and loving, Zoran is the cutest little guy and would be a wonderful addition to any home. 

Zoran is a pint-sized snuggle bug who loves to burrow under a blanket or lay next to you when you're watching TV or reading. When you are busy with household duties or are busy teleworking, he is content to play with his favorite squeaky toy or ball. Zoran has mastered vocalizing his needs and will let you know with his sweet squeals that he is either hungry, needs to go out or wants a scratch. You will know he has complete trust in you when he throws his little head back like a seal to receive your scratches, specifically on his neck. Or, he will bounce from his adorably stumpy but agile legs to let you know he wants to be held. Zoran is non-reactive to other dogs when being walked and shares space and attention well with his two foster dog siblings, and is showing more interest in playing with them. He is okay with respectful children over 12 years old. 

The best adopters for Zoran are patient people who will continue his development of becoming a happy, balanced dog. Zoran is 9 pounds and about 3 years old. Fill out an application today to meet him.

animal.description: Ginger is a sweet, mellow pit bull mix, who is 7 years old. She was surrendered to the Animal Shelter because she didn't get along with cats and other dogs. However, at the Shelter, she has been out to several playgroups with other dogs and has done well with other gentle dogs. Ginger is not playful with other dogs, but she should be able to coexist with another mellow dog in her next home that will give her plenty of space. Ginger will make an excellent low energy companion for her person and prefers quietly hanging out at your side. This sweet girl knows how to sit on command and loves attention from people. She will likely do best in a home she can retire in that is quiet and has no cats or young children to make her uncomfortable, since she once nipped at a young child, who made her uncomfortable in her previous home. At 75 pounds, Ginger could lose a few, so she would benefit from a healthy diet and regular exercise. Her next owner should also be strong enough to handle her when she occasionally pulls on her leash. Ginger must meet other dogs in the home prior to adoption. If you can provide Ginger what she needs and give her a loving home, please call Michelle at 510-589-7341. Her adoption fee has already been prepaid by a generous donor, so the only cost to adopt is $25 for an annual dog license, if you live in Jackson County!

animal.description: My name is Vincent! I'm a typical husky, which means I have high energy, smarts, sometimes a high prey drive and a mischievous personality. I need daily mental and physical exercise with a consistent routine, otherwise my mischievous side gets a little ornerier, which means I may find inappropriate ways to expel my energy like chewing on things I shouldn't or being an escape artist; something we huskies tend to be experts at. I can be sensitive when it comes to some handling, I'm not a huge fan of being grabbed and tugged on. I may do better in a home with older children that are at least 6 years old and have a family that will understand that grabbing my collar to make me do something would be very overwhelming and scary for me. I can also be a bit nervous when startled or meeting new people, but go slow and use treats, I can get comfortable pretty easily. I'm definitely more on the aloof side of the husky spectrum, however once I get more comfortable, you'll see the more affectionate side of my personality. I can be vocal when I'm left alone so cannot live in an apartment where others may not be as appreciative of my singing voice. If you're well versed in the husky ways and looking for love and excitement in your life, I'm your kind of companion! I need to meet all family members and dogs in the home to make sure it's a perfect match. Vincent will be shown by appointment only. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . Be sure to include Vincent 1259251 when filling out the survey. After reviewing your application, we will only be reaching out to you if the animal is a good fit for your home.

Meet Sammi.

This sweet girl is looking for a very special home. Sammi came to us as a new mom from a very scary situation. When Sammi first came to us she was extremely shut down and what we consider semi feral.

Sammi has certainly come a long way since being with us but is still in desperate need of a very calm and patient home that will go slow and continue to work on socializing and building her confidence. 

Sammi is very sweet but very apprehensive about being touched. She is very shy with strangers and takes some time to open up. She is currently on a medication for her anxiety and will probably need to stay on this medication for a while, possibly for life.

Sammi is a professional escape artist and will most likely need to be watched outside at all times. Because she is so fearful, Sammi will need a home with no young children. She has not been reactive towards dogs here in a negative or positive way but we believe that having a confident dog in the home may help her come out of her shell a bit more.

Because Sammi is so fearful we really want to see her in a low traffic home preferably with someone who has worked with extremely fearful/semi feral dogs before.  She will need a lot of patience and understanding but we are confident with the right family she will blossom into a happy dog!!


Our adoption fees include the pets spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccines, heartworm/tick disease testing and fecal check.  All adoption fees can be found on our groups' Petfinder page. 
The first step to our adoption process is to please fill out and adoptions application, it can be found on our website www.serenityanimalhospital.net, under the "Adopt From Us" Tab.
Please email the application to adoptions@serenityanimalhospital.net or drop it off in person during our business hours. Any questions regarding our adoptable dogs can be emailed along with your application.  Please allow us a few days to contact you about your application as we do get many in on a daily basis.  We will contact you as soon as possible.

animal.description:
Marbles is a very friendly boy.  He gets along with other dogs.  We do not know what he thinks of cats.  He was turned in along with his brother Koda #2.  Marbles tested positive for Lyme's.  He is on a course of oral antibiotic which he can complete with his new family.  Marbles is still available for adoption at this time.   Marbles is about 8 months old and 42 pounds.

***You must provide a vet reference for a current or past pet you have/had.***

We do NOT ship our animals. All adoptive families must travel to us to meet their adoptive dog/cat. Applicants must live within a 2 hour radius from Sparta/Andover (07871/07821).

Please understand that we are an animal shelter and thus unable to say whether the dogs are housebroken as they are not in homes.

If you are interested in adopting, we encourage you to please submit an application on our website today so that we can try and process and pre-approve any potential adopters prior to our next adoption event.

PLEASE USE THIS LINK TO SUBMIT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION. WE ONLY ACCEPT ADOPTION APPLICATIONS THROUGH OUR WEBSITE. ANY OTHERS WILL NOT BE PROCESSED.
Application link here: http://www.oscaranimalrescue.org/oscar-1-application.html

Adoption Process:
1.Fill out an application
2.Meet & Greet
3.Adoption contract & adoption fee
Marbles' adoption fee is $425. This also covers all age-appropriate shots, spay/neuter, vetting & microchipping.

**If you are coming to an adoption event to see a certain dog/cat, please email ahead of time to make sure that dog/cat will be there that day. Please email 1-2 days before the event, as some animals are placed during the week and our list is constantly changing.
For a list of upcoming pet adoption events go to: www.OscarAnimalRescue.org

One Step Closer Animal Rescue is a 501c3 non-profit organization. Donations are TAX DEDUCTIBLE to the extent allowed by law. If you would like to make a donation to help us rescue more animals please send donations to PO Box 248, Sparta, NJ 07871. Please make your check payable to O.S.C.A.R.. Thank you for helping us save as many lives as we can.

https://www.facebook.com/pages/One-Step-Closer-Animal-Rescue-OSCAR/462492563811538

She loves going for walks, treats, and chewing on toys. Gabby gets along well with the large dogs and cat in her current foster home, but does best with more relaxed animals and sometimes needs reminded to back down if play gets too exciting. She also does best with dogs her size or larger (no small dogs, please!). Gabby would do best with humans and animals that respect her space at times when she wants left alone and are willing to make sure she has comfy spaces to lounge and cuddle so older children (12+) will be the best match.

Gabby's adoption fee is $250 and includes her spay, microchip and current vaccinations and preventatives PLUS a free basic obedience course at Cedar Run Pet Boarding & Daycare in Hiawatha. Last Hope requires that all animals be kept as indoor pets only, be altered and current on vaccinations and preventatives. Meet MOOSE NASH!! If you are a BIG dog lover, than Moose is your guy!! Moose is Lab mix estimated to be about 1 year old and weighs a whopping 82 pounds.

Moose is a big boy who is VERY VERY sweet. He loves everyone he meets and gets along well with other dogs and cats too. Moose is house-trained and mostly crate-trained. He doesn't love to be in the crate, but will go in one if he has to. Moose is a smart dog and would benefit from some training. His fosters have already taught him the sit command. He is great with kids, but because of his size he could easily knock down a smaller child by accident. He would love a big yard with a tall fence so he could learn to play fetch. His perfect family would be a young, active couple who is willing to spend time hiking, walking and giving him plenty of exercise. They would be paid back with lots of love and loyalty. Won't you open your heart and home to this loving, goofy guy?

To meet MOOSE NASH, please complete an adoption application at www.ehrdogs.org and ask for him by name.

Koda#2 is a very friendly boy.  He gets along with other dogs.  We do not know what he thinks of cats.  He was turned in along with his brother Marbles.  Koda#2 tested positive for Lyme's.  He is on a course of oral antibiotic which he can complete with his new family.  Koda#2 is still available for adoption at this time.   Koda#2 is about 8 months old and 35 pounds.

Please note that we currently have 2 dogs with similar names.  Please refer to "Koda#2" in your application/correspondence about this dog to avoid any delays/confusions.

***You must provide a vet reference for a current or past pet you have/had.***

We do NOT ship our animals. All adoptive families must travel to us to meet their adoptive dog/cat. Applicants must live within a 2 hour radius from Sparta/Andover (07871/07821).

Please understand that we are an animal shelter and thus unable to say whether the dogs are housebroken as they are not in homes.

If you are interested in adopting, we encourage you to please submit an application on our website today so that we can try and process and pre-approve any potential adopters prior to our next adoption event.

PLEASE USE THIS LINK TO SUBMIT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION. WE ONLY ACCEPT ADOPTION APPLICATIONS THROUGH OUR WEBSITE. ANY OTHERS WILL NOT BE PROCESSED.
Application link here: http://www.oscaranimalrescue.org/oscar-1-application.html

Adoption Process:
1.Fill out an application
2.Meet & Greet
3.Adoption contract & adoption fee
Koda#2's adoption fee is $425. This also covers all age-appropriate shots, spay/neuter, vetting & microchipping.

**If you are coming to an adoption event to see a certain dog/cat, please email ahead of time to make sure that dog/cat will be there that day. Please email 1-2 days before the event, as some animals are placed during the week and our list is constantly changing.
For a list of upcoming pet adoption events go to: www.OscarAnimalRescue.org

One Step Closer Animal Rescue is a 501c3 non-profit organization. Donations are TAX DEDUCTIBLE to the extent allowed by law. If you would like to make a donation to help us rescue more animals please send donations to PO Box 248, Sparta, NJ 07871. Please make your check payable to O.S.C.A.R.. Thank you for helping us save as many lives as we can.

animal.description:
I love to SING!
My favorite activity, other than loving on humans, is singing. I love to joyfully sing the Bloodhound Bay. 
I am looking for a family that appreciates the deep bay that I sing when I am happy.
I am a big boy, and really still a puppy...I need some one willing to invest time with me in training.
I do have Bloodhound Attention deficit disorder, this is when my nose takes over for my brain, and I can only concentrate on where my nose directs me... this disorder has now earned me the no recall award...but I am working on doing better.
I do not challenge fences, but will happily run out of the gate to meet you at the car, if the opportunity arises.
I am also working on leash manners, seems like I am in a bigger hurry to get to the destination faster than what my humans can walk...
Now for my positives.. I will give you unconditionally love, my early are silky soft, and I will curl up on the couch with you to cuddle in front of the TV.
I would love to meet my new family soon...

Darla is about a year old and a very sweet and active girl! She is a 15 lb. terrier mix who was was rescued from Mexico and is now spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, and looking for her forever family. She gets along with other dogs but is a dominant female so would do best with a submissive male as her partner in crime.

Darla is still learning basic commands and leash walking. She is doing very well with potty training and loves to be with her person whether it’s snuggling on the couch or going on a walk.

We suggest a home with children over the age of 10 for this dog. This dog cannot be adopted out of state. Please see our home page for a list of our Saturday adoption sites. Every potential adopter is required to fill out an adoption application, and the dog is placed in the home that would be most suitable for the dog. We do not place our dogs in homes with unfenced swimming pools. Generally we don't release the dogs at the adoption site that day except on occasion to former adopters.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please contact us at FCIAadoptions@aol.com or call 619-466-9137. Due to the pandemic we are now requiring all interested people to fill out our application at www.FCIAnimals.org. If we think it is a good match, we will arrange an introduction.

Hello everyone! My name is buster! I am a yellow lab mix and I’m 8 months old! I am so sweet and I absolutely love my doggy friends here in the rescue! I can’t wait to be adopted into my very own family. I am house and crate trained. I’m so cute and sweet! 

The adoption donation fee is $400 which is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with Pals for Paws. 

To expedite the adoption process you can fill out an application online at www.palsforpawsinc.com/adopt. Please note the adoption application doesn’t bind you to anything. Pals for Paws reserves the right to refuse any adoption application for any reason and at any point in the adoption process. 

To view our other wonderful Homeless Pets visit www.palsforpawsinc.com/pet-list ALSO be sure to LIKE Pals for Paws on Facebook at www.facebook.com/palsforpaws.inc 

All Pals for Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Groomed
*Shots updated plus Leptospirosis 
*Micro-chipped
*Dewormed 
*On Heart-worm prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention
* Dentals are done if needed 

You only need to see your vet for a “meet n greet” of your new family member and to turn in their medical records.

Pals for Paws is a 501(c)3 animal rescue. Every penny donated and every penny received through adoption fees goes right back into the organization. There are times when the volunteers have to dip into their pockets to help the animals. We do not euthanize because a pet is sick, heart-worm positive, or has a broken leg; we fix it all, big and small. We strive to go above and beyond when caring for and socializing our animals. We understand the importance of getting to know each and every animal available for adoption in an effort to place them in the most perfect home possible. 
If you are looking for a particular type of dog or have special needs, We can help! Contact us at www.palsforpawsinc.com

Hey everybody, the name is Remy! I became an Underdog because I was having some health issues but those are all cleared up now and I'm finally ready to start looking for my forever home.

Being a young adult comes with some perks; I am fully house trained and I can be trusted loose outside of my kennel and I've been working hard on my leash manners. I would love it if you could help me keep working on that! I am not a fan of other dogs or cats. Young kids are just too loud and scary for me and sometimes I don't know my own size so a home with older kids (12+) or that I can be solo with my human is really what I need. I LOVE to go for walks and staying active to help keep me focused. This is especially important so I pay attention during training. Speaking of, I need someone who is going to keep helping me work on myself. When I came in to care I was pretty reactive on a leash but I've come leaps and bounds since then. I definitely have some more work to do but so long as I have you in my corner, working on it with me, I'm sure I'll continue to improve! Going to the vet is terrifying sometimes because new people can be scary when I can't have my personal space so I've learned how to wear a muzzle so that I can be more confident while there.

I'm a silly goofball who truly loves cuddles, can I sit on your lap? I think we would make a great family so if you're the active type of family who wants to continue learning with me, you should apply to meet me!

Classes I have completed with Pliant Pack:
Reactive K9 - 4 week online course
Leash Manners - 4 week online course

PLEASE NOTE: Because we do not have a public shelter, an adoption application must be filled out in order to be approved to meet any of our animals available for adoption. No exceptions. Serious inquiries only.

animal.description:
"Hi, Y'all! Have you ever seen a dog as adorable as me?! Can you believe I’m homeless and am waiting for a wonderful person or family to adopt me? Great dogs like me end up in animal shelters every day- I know, it’s so hard to believe but it’s true!

My name is Noble, and I just joined the adoptable doggy crew at Providence Animal Center from Pensacola, FL. I'm around 4 years old, curvy 59 pounds, and I'm all set to move right into your heart & home today - already spayed, microchipped & up to date on vaccinations. 

I was found as a stray and soon delivered 11 puppies. Now that they have been weaned off, I am ready to find a home of my own. My FL foster has the following to say about me:

"Noble is a sweet and easy going girl. She housebroken and knows sit and down (though sometimes she's stubborn and likes to "forget" this one). She is very treat/food motivated and loves toys that use her brain -- munchy mats, kongs, and other puzzle toys. She has been excited to meet everyone. She enjoys sunbathing, but her favorite thing is to curl up next to you on the couch for a nap"

The staff would love to match you with your new best friend forever - and hopefully that's me! If you are interested in meeting me in person, please schedule an appointment here: ProvidenceAC.org/AdoptADog. My paws are crossed I will see you very soon! XOXO Noble"

-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!

Please note: Some pets are still in fabulous foster homes, so be sure to check the pet’s ‘location’ in their listing prior to scheduling an appointment. To meet a pet currently in a foster home, follow the instructions listed in their bio. Thank you for your flexibility during this challenging time! We can’t wait to see your masked face!

Providence Animal Center relies on adoption fees and donations to save pets! Adoption fees vary per pet. To find out this pet’s adoption fee or for more information, please call the Adoption Center with this pet’s ID number.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Adoption fee is $250. Apply at www.straypawsrescue.com

Prior to foster: Raider was on the euthanasia list at a shelter. He was an owner surrender but not much was known about him. The previous owners neighbor did share on social media that Raider was great with kids and other dogs and was just a gentle giant. During Foster: Raider came to us in 2020 as our Covid Foster. We thought he was around 5 years old based on info from the shelter he was pulled from but the vet here thinks he may be closer to 3 years old. He is crate trained and very motivated by treats to go into the kennel. He is house trained and even lets you know sometimes when he needs to go out but we keep him on a pretty regular schedule. He is a 75 lb lap dog who I affectionately refer to as a snuggle moose. He literally can't get close enough sometimes and personal space is non-existent in Raider's world. He is really great with older kids. Due to his size he may not be the best with younger kids. Our 5 year old loved him but sometimes he would ignore her or if he got hyped up he would knock her over. So it was nothing due to aggression just he doesn't realize his size. He would do really well with space to run. He still has a bit of that puppy energy and occasionally gets bursts of energy and if he doesn't have space to let it out he is a complete bull in a china shop. He is pretty much a big lovable doofus though and would make the perfect pet for a family with time for him.

FAST FACTS:
*6-7 Years Old - 80 Pounds
*Gentle, Affectionate Personality
*Dog Friendly
*Potty & Crate Trained

BIO:
Here ye, here ye, if you are looking for a regal friend with a big smile and a hind end that never stops wagging, you have come to the right place! My name is Queenie, and I'm a gentle, sweet lady who loves body massages and lounging with my people. But I also have a playful streak and love romping and rolling with my doggie friends. I have lovely manners: I am potty trained, crate trained, and walk great on a leash. I'm so happy and friendly that I think I would do fine with children, as well. I hope you fill out an adoption application soon because I would love to share my big heart and endless affection with you!

ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS, NO EXCEPTIONS:
*ADOPTION FEE: $300
*Be at least 21 years of age
*Live in a 50-mile radius of Itasca, within the Illinois border
*Have the knowledge and agreement of all adults living in the household
*Have approval from owner of residence (written in lease)
*Have a valid ID with current address (please provide proof of address if ID address is not up-to-date)
*Be approved as a suitable adoptive home by Fetching Tails Foundation
*Be prepared to make a lifetime commitment

If interested please fill out an application on our website at www.fetchingtailsfoundation.org; please make sure you fill in every required field/question or your submission will not go through. Please note that we take time to learn as much as we can about each dog in our care and our bios are our current observations; we are unable to make any guarantees on the future health or temperament of your adopted dog. Most dogs in our care come with unknown pre-rescue history and as such breed and age estimates are an educated guess.

animal.description:
Meet  Benjamin and Grant  ~

Our names are Benjamin and Grant. We are Border Collie/Lab mixes from South Carolina.  We weigh roughly 45 lbs. and are 9-12 months old.

We were found by a very nice woman that kept us safe at the veterinary clinic where she worked until we were able to be adopted out. There was nowhere for us to go while in SC, so we stayed at the clinic every day. The staff there was very nice to us! They were so busy and didn't have much time to play with us unfortunately. But, whenever they had time, they took us for walks and did fun stuff with us!
 Loving people as much as we do, it was hard not to be with them all the time! We just cannot wait for homes of our own!

*The adoption fee for each pup is $500.00. The boys do not have to be adopted together.

With my adorable looks, and unbridled loyalty, I will always be there for you through thick and thin. I will never judge you, or turn my back on you. Every single day, you will look at me and you will know that you are loved unconditionally. I will never betray you or hurt you, and I will grow old by your side.

******IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ ALL THE GREAT INFO BELOW******

***Please don't apply unless you are very serious about adopting, and are ready to move forward with the adoption process. We are super busy and make a great effort to respond back to EVERYONE ASAP! WHEN WE TAKE THE TIME TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION AND RESPOND BACK TO THE APPLICANT JUST TO BE EITHER IGNORED OR BE TOLD THEY CANNOT COME FOR SEVERAL DAYS, MORE TIME IS WASTED~PLEASE HAVE MORE RESPECT THAN THAT!

PLEASE read our website's ADOPTION PROCESS PAGE prior to submitting an adoption application. www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-process 
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-application 

ABOUT OUR RESCUE DOGS: 
 All of our dogs are located in Connecticut, are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, have been given deworming medications, and have had CT State health checks, & go home with a leash, collar, & packet of medical paperwork. 

BREED IDENTIFICATION:
Please understand that many rescue dogs are mixes of multiple breeds. Petfinder allows us to choose up to two breeds per dog. While the shelters and our rescue do our best in accurately identifying breeds, breed identification is not guaranteed. If there is a certain breed that you do not want, it is very important that you share this with our rescue when applying. When adopting a puppy, breed uncertainty plays a big part in the size/look of the dog as an adult. Please know that any puppy can be a wonderful dog, regardless of preconceived notions of certain breeds, but it is very important that the adopter has the dedication and patience to raise the puppy with boundaries, consistency, structure, & love. The more effort you give towards training & time you allow for exercise, your puppy will grow to be a HUGE source of UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, TOTAL LOYALTY, HAPPINESS, COMFORT & COMPANIONSHIP!

ABOUT OUR RESCUE:
We are a small rescue run by volunteers & focused on finding the right match for both our dogs & for you. If you are interested in adopting through our rescue, you first will need to complete an adoption application & be approved as a potential adopter before meeting any of our pups. No need to be intimidated by our application as it allows us to get to know you & your lifestyle. Of course, the more you can share the better! Please also note, while a fenced yard is fantastic, it is not required by our rescue, however, it may be required for a certain dog occasionally.  Once adoption applicants are approved to become potential adopters, we offer private appointments where you can meet one or several dogs at the discretion of the rescue. We offer a unique & pleasant experience focused on finding the perfect match. It is extremely important to us that everyone is treated with respect & that NO ONE IS LEFT HANGING. WE WILL GET BACK TO YOU WITHIN 2 TO 3 DAYS of application submission. If there is a dog you are eager to meet, please  TEXT US DIRECTLY at 203-241-2351 so that we can check the status of your application and move it forward immediately. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new best friend.

*All adult dogs can be cat tested by request.

HOME/RENTER INSURANCE:
SOME PROVIDERS HAVE VERY STRICT POLICIES REGARDING WHICH TYPE OF DOG BREEDS ARE ALLOWED UNDER THEIR COVERAGE. STATE FARM WAS SUGGESTED TO US AS THEY DO NOT PUNISH, DROP, NOR REFUSE YOU DUE TO DOG BREED SHOULD YOU RUN INTO ISSUES WITH YOUR CURRENT PROVIDER.

animal.description:
***Excelsior is available only through our Foster to Adopt Program***

Hi! I'm Excelsior! 

If you are looking for a sweet, caring and loving dog you should pick me!!! I am one of the sweetest girls around. My foster mom says whoever picks me has the equivalent of winning the lottery. I am a gentle soul and love to be around my people. I also enjoy the company of other dogs but would do great as the only dog in the house as well. 

I am fully potty trained and eat and sleep in my kennel. I will come up to you and place my paw on your lap to let you know I would like some pets. Then, once I get my pets and scratches, I look at you like you are the only person in the world. I love chew toys so they are a must for me. I like running around outside so a fenced in yard is preferred. I am a gentle giant that is good with all ages, but sometimes I forget my size and think I am still a puppy. For this reason, my foster mom would suggest me going to a home with children over 3. 

I am super excited to meet you so I can be on my way to my furever home!!

***Foster to Adopt*** 
Excelsior is available through our Foster to Adopt program because she is not yet spayed. Her spay is scheduled for the beginning of February at our vets in Minnetonka. The spay will be covered by the rescue. All of the medical expenses will be paid for by the rescue while she is in a foster to adopt home, however, the foster to adopt applicant will be excpected to pay 50% of the adoption fee at the time they take the pup into their home to foster. 

--------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

*** Remi is available for adoption in our Foster to Adopt Program ***


Hi! My name is Remi....cute name huh? I am an adorable and timid little lady who has traveled all the way from Alabama to find my new forever home. 

I am the sweetest little gal. My favorite thing to do is sit on your lap and cuddle. I have a few kids at my foster home. They are sweet but I prefer the adults. I am potty trained. One thing I am NOT sure of is all this white stuff on the ground. It sure is cold in Minnesota! I go out to potty and then go right back in. I also have a little coat I wear and that helps a little. 

I have a mellow personality. My perfect day consists of napping and snuggling. There are 2 other dogs that live at my foster house. I don't really think anything of them. One has tried to play with me and I have politely declined. 

If you think I may be the one for for you I would love to meet! 



FOSTER TO ADOPT:
Remi just completed Heartworm treatment and is waiting for a negative test result which can take 2-9 months after treatment. During these months, she will need to make sure her heart rate is not elevated due to high energy play or exercise. Remi is only available through the Foster to Adopt Program at this time. The commitment will be for an adoption but will be fostering until she is cleared with a negative Heartworm test result. All of the medical expenses will be paid for by the rescue while she is in a foster to adopt home, however, the foster to adopt applicant will be excpected to pay 50% of the adoption fee at the time they take the pup into their home to foster. Food, kennel, grooming and other supplies will be provided by the foster in the foster to adopt program. 

--------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. animal.description:
Hi, my name is Lena. I am loving Minnesota and am curious about the cold white stuff on the ground. 

My foster mom is working with me on some basic things like sit, down, wait, off, and bed. I've learned that my kennel is not such a bad place and do well while in mine. I lived with another dog previously and he helped me to learn these things too. We had a lot of fun outside in the yard playing tag, wrestling, and smelling what animals had been there. We also liked just hanging out inside together on our beds. It would be great if I had a companion dog in my forever home but I do just fine without one as well. As long as my human give me lots of love, I will do great! 

My foster mom says that I would do best in an active home. I love going for hikes and adventures in the great wide open. If you gave me a job to do I would be happy to learn it! Keeping my mind and body active will benefit everyone! There is so much fun to be had! I can't wait to see where my new life takes me!

Some of my favorite things are hugs and snuggles on the couch. If you make me a part of your family we would make each other very happy and I will be forever loyal and grateful. Can't wait to meet you and show you all the love I have in my heart!

Hello! My name is Nelson, but you can call me Perfect! Yep, that's me. I am so good my foster mama says I'm perfect. When I am let out to potty, I always go; I have not had any accidents in the house. I sit when my breakfast and dinner are being served. I lay on my bed or under the table when my foster family is eating - no begging, it's not polite. I sleep very well in my kennel, and I LOVE to snuggle, preferably on the couch or bed. Really, what more could you ask for? 

Currently, I live with my foster mom and dad, four boy humans (ages: 18, 17, 13, and 12) and a Golden Retriever resident dog. I love ALL of them! I have tried to play with the resident dog, but she isn't very playful. It's okay though because I need to stay calm since I am heartworm positive. I had heartworm treatment when I was in Alabama and am doing well. If you are interested in adopting me, you will ""foster-to-adopt"" me. If you aren't sure what that is, make sure to ask.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Drake. According to my foster family, I am a very cool guy. Not sure what that means, but I'm told it's a good thing. I am ready to be your pal in whatever you're up to. I'm ready to play, I love my squeaky toys, but if you're chilling on the couch, I'm totally up for some snuggles too. I love walks, I'm pretty good at not pulling, and I LOVE this white stuff y'all have here. It is so much fun to jump in, eat (just the white stuff, thank you), and sniff! The cold never bothered me anyway.

I love my foster family a lot too. I stay close in case they need me, sometimes I'll make sure they see my head so they can relieve some stress by scratching my ears. It's win-win, they get to scratch, and i get scratched! Best idea ever. The shorter foster family humans are great too. I'm pretty good around them, i want to make sure they are willing to give me belly rubs, so I snuggle in and sloooowly roll over until they see my belly, works every time. 

I like my canine foster brother too, he's kind of old, but he's taught me some good things about being a part of a family, so I'm happy to be with him. We never fight. After a while I get tired from all the playing, and making sure my humans are stress-free via belly rubs and ear scritches, so when the humans are away, I hang out in my crate, and to be honest, I like the alone time. 

My foster parents say I know how to take care of business, I always make sure it's outside in the yard, or while I'm taking my leash for a walk. I'm doing pretty well in school. I have an ""A"" in sit and down. I found out I have an A+ in vocal restraint too. I started a new unit on stay and wait, but I'm figuring it out. 

If you are looking for a softie who is up for play or snuggles, likes long walks in the snow, I am definitely your guy. I can't wait to meet you!

animal.description:
Hello, my name is Sampson! WHOA - that was a long car ride from AL to MN! It's taken me a few days to recover from the big road trip, but I'm coming around. Some of my favorite activities right now are sleeping in my kennel, sleeping on my blanket next to my kennel in my foster Mom's office, watching TV ( with my eyes closed) next to my foster family, and hanging out in the kitchen. I'm an excellent vacuum.. But don't worry, I have the BEST manners, my foster Mom keeps telling my foster brothers to take notes. I don't jump up on people, I don't bark when the doorbell rings, I don't jump up on the furniture. I can sit and lay down, and I LOVE belly rubs.
 
My foster Mom thinks I was maybe a country boy. I walk really nice on my leash and don't pull, swerve all around, or piddle on every pole or mailbox we pass. I just trot along. Lots of traffic makes me kinda nervous, even when we're on sidewalks, I prefer a more serene atmosphere. I'm pretty darn good about my bathroom habits - no accidents in the house. Not bad for a country boy! I can't take all the credit, my foster family is always asking me if I need to go potty and takes me outside frequently.

My foster family has a Dad, Mom, and teenage girl I really really like, and 2 dogs and 2 cats. I love all the people, the cats and I have an agreement - be cool, I don't pay attention to you, you don't pay attention to me. The 2 dogs are fun to watch, but I'm just not 100% sure why we all need to play together. I like to observe, but I don't like it when they try to make me play with them. I'd rather hang on the sidelines for now. 

If you're looking for some leash candy - easy on the eyes, sweet as can be, and likes quiet companionship with snuggles, I'm your boy!

Please contact Sonya (srstewart159@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.

This is Patsy! A min pin mix around a year old. She is sweet, playful and affectionate. She came to us from another shelter so her background is unknown. Guessing she lived in a home before. She requires lots of pets and if you aren't petting her enough she will let you know by nudging your hand or getting close to your face. She also seems to be already crated trained and almost house trained. She has done great out of the crate at night and likes to sleep in the bed. She also knows sit and will come to a whistle. Patsy has done well with the dog and cat in the foster home. Her favorite things include cuddling, playing with stuffed toys, more pets, following you around the house to make sure your okay and rolling around in blankets.

Things to considered when thinking about applying to adopt Patsy:

She is still young and learning things. Like not to chew or get on the table.

She has a moderate energy level. She will need some playtime or walks daily

She loves to be a lap dog and cuddle. She will probably also be in your personal space.

She hasn't been around kids in her current foster home. Guessing she would be just fine. Might need some extra training to learn how to be more gentle. She likes to use her paws when playing.

Sometimes she gets jealous when you are petting other dogs and will also make sure she is getting attention. She isn't aggressive about but will make sure you are petting her too and might even get a paw in the face. :)

She is a Velcro dog! She will follow you everywhere. She needs the right person to build her confidence!

She has a loud high pitched bark. An apartment/condo/townhouse wouldn't be best

If your home/lifestyle fits Patsy, please complete the
required adoption application at www.pawsandprayers.org. The foster listed will contact you if your application is approved and set up a meet and greet. Patsy adoption fee is $350. She is micro chipped, current on vaccines, heart worm negative, spayed, and current on flea/tick/heart worm prevention

check out more photos and videos here;

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Age:
Approximately 1- 1 years old

Weight:
53 pounds

Adoption Fee:
$350

Crate trained:
She will go into her crate, often when it's open to rest and relax. She does not like to be in the crate in general when the door is closed. We believe she could be crate trained.

Potty trained:
Yes

Dog friendly:
Yes

Cat friendly:
Unknown

Kid friendly:
Unknown

Apartment/condo appropriate?
Perhaps, if she received regular walks and exercise.

Appropriate for 1st-time dog owners?:
Julie would work best with someone who has had a dog previously or someone who has been around dogs. Also, she will do better if at least one person is home most of the day with her or she is home with another dog. At least at this younger age, we don't think she's a dog that will do well left alone for long periods of time. She loves companionship.

Energy level:
Low to medium. She plays, likes walks, and exercise, but also likes her chill time.

Require a fence?:
Not required, but Julie would benefit from a fenced area to run. Absent a fence, the people who adopt her should be willing to provide ample walks and exercise.

Enjoy's car rides?:
She is fine in the car.

Training adopter needs to work on:

Build confidence and overcome shyness.

Barking at the window, it's not incessant, but something to be worked on

Heeling on walks. She's OK, but could improve and tends to tug if she sees something she's interested in.

Personality Summary for Julie:

She is shy at first, but once she gets to know you, she is friendly, affectionate, and loves to play.

She loves being with people.

She loves toys and will fetch and play tug-of-war.

She loves to exercise, both on-leash and running in our small front yard.

She is not an incessant barker but will bark to alert if she sees someone or something out the window.

She does not tend to bark on-leash, even when passing other people or dogs.

She's smart and already knows how to sit and shake paws. And she's working on stay.

Even at her young age, she is one of the most affectionate and better-behaved fosters we have had.

Please review our adoption process, fees & complete an application at

www.hoofwoofmeow.org

to learn more about Julie! (Please use a computer if possible to complete the application vs your phone.) Thank you!

animal.description: Meet Harley! This 3-year-old boy is revving his engine because he's ready to find his forever home! animal.description:
Hi, my name is Rosie and Im a mid-sized Hound mix! I am almost two years old and am looking for a forever home. I am very loving and sweet with everyone I meet and am looking to get lots of hugs and snuggles. I love kids, I love other dogs, and I even love cats! My ideal home would be one with a fenced-in yard and perhaps kids and other pets too because I have a lot of energy and friendship to give. I do very well on a leash and am very easily potty-trained! I also know how to sit, stay, shake, down, and roll-over! I am hoping to find an active family that likes to include me in their daily life. I love walks and a run at the dog park or the yard. Please ask to meet me; I cant wait to meet you! 
 

We believe this dog is a Hound mix and was born on 4/17/2019. This puppy is fostered in a private home in Lincoln. The adoption fee is $300.00 which covers vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter(when old enough). The adoption fee helps cover the cost of these vetting procedures. Unless the bio is marked adoption pending, s/he is still available for adoption. If youre interested in adopting this puppy, please submit an inquiry or email BraveAnimalRescue@gmail.com to ask about our adoption process (please check your spam or junk email if you do not hear back from us within a few business days). We are 100% volunteer staffed and will respond to your email as soon as possible. After you have submitted an application and been approved, we will set up a meet and greet between you and the puppy. Preference is given to applicants with a verifiable vetting history, fenced yard, and homeownership. Please be sure to follow us on Facebook and Instagram to learn more about Brave Animal Rescue and our mission.

animal.description:
IVY is an affectionate sweet mini Lab mix mamma. She is playful, loves to be petted and be with her humans and gets along well with dogs.

Her adoption fee includes her spaying, vaccines, deworming, microchip. She was born on a reservation we work with 2019. She still needs basic training and leash training. She has a daughter Fern for your consideration that came into the rescue with her.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Meet Sweet Janet Jackson aka "JJ". JJ was found dumpster diving for food, starving (weighing only 14 pounds), very pregnant, and injured in her hips. With the help of several very dedicated volunteers, she was brought from Calexico to our Arizona rescue ranch.

Within one week she went into labor but was unable to naturally have the pups. She was rushed to a vet who performed a C-section. The vet found 9 puppies and a raging bacterial infection inside of little JJ. Only three of her puppies survived. Even with all of her difficulties she was the best mama, patiently raising her three pups, who have been adopted.

Our fabulous orthopedic surgeon performed hip surgery on JJ several months ago and she is now healthy and playing and running with her foster sisters. 

She is still a small dog weighing less than 30 pounds, and is very sweet, loving and thoughtful. She shares well with her foster siblings with both food and toys.
JJ is very special and deserves a loving home. She loves all adults and children, is very calm, and alerts only if there is a reason.

Won't you consider bringing home this beautiful girl?"

animal.description:
Although Cooper may be a little older than the usual rescue dog, that doesn't slow him down. This ten year old poodle LOVES a good puppichino, chicken (he will do anything for a tasty piece of chicken), and to snuggle. His most favorite of all, though, is to join his people on car rides. Look at that huge smile in the car! He is fully house trained and has slight separation anxiety. Cooper really enjoys company and would rather spend his doggy senior years with cuddles rather than crates. Cooper is looking for an owner that is home a lot and is wanting good lap time. He also enjoys walking and playing with doggy friends. 
Cooper is going blind, so will benefit from an Adopter who understands senior Littles. He will need additional patients to help him decompress.

Please inquire by submitting an application to Shannon@threelittlepittiesrescue.org.

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/21588/generic 
 

The adoption fee is $200. He is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee J.

Due to the Covid-19 crisis we are experiencing a dramatic influx in inquiries and adoption applications. If you have questions regarding a pup you are interested in please fill out an adoption application. Once received it can take up to a week to complete our review. Be assured we have received your received your application! If you need more information regarding a pup you are interested in, the process of filling out an adoption application is still required prior to answering detailed questions. We value our potential adopters time and appreciate your patience as our staff navigate through the blessing of an overwhelming response for adoptions.

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families. www.threelittlepittiesrescue.org

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN FOSTERING THIS PET, PLEASE COMPLETE A FOSTER APPLICATION FOUND ON OUR WEBSITE HTTP://FUREVERTAILS.COM/HELP/FOSTER.

MEET PUDDIN:

Puddin is a 1yr old, 40lb Aussie/Lab mix. She entered a high intake shelter as a stray. She is dog and people friendly, but has not yet been exposed to cats. Puddin will not be a good fit for an apartment/condo lifestyle or mobile home community as this is a working class breed dog and is very active. She will require a fenced in yard. Puddin is house-trained and learned quickly to go to the patio door and stare longingly at her foster parents to be let out. She loves to spend her time on the couch cuddling and getting belly rubs. Puddin loves chewing on Nylabones and chasing a tennis ball in the yard and getting the "zoomies" in the snow! She still has a few puppy qualities, like chewing, but re-directs quickly and easily with a firm "no" and being handed her Nylabone. She is learning to walk on a leash wearing a harness. Puddin is starting to learn basic commands. She would benefit from living in a house where her family were home more often than not since she doesn't like to be crated and has escaped from her crate. Puddin respects baby gates for the areas her foster parents did not want her to go while they are home. Puddin is looking for a furever home with a active family that is experienced and would love to spend time with her. 

Puddin is:
Current on Rabies and Distemper
Dewormed
Heartworm Tested: Negative
Receiving Heartworm and Flea Prevention
Microchipped
Will be spayed prior to adoption.

ADOPTION FEE: $300

FUREVER TAILS IS A NON-PROFIT, NO-KILL, FOSTER HOME BASED ANIMAL RESCUE BASED OUT OF OAKLAND TOWNSHIP, MI. OUR FOSTER ANIMALS ARE LIVING IN FOSTER HOMES AND TREATED LIKE FAMILY UNTIL THEY FIND THEIR OWN FUREVER FAMILIES. OUR ADOPTION PROECESS REQUIRES AN APPLICATION TO BE COMPLETED AND APPROVED BEFORE A MEET-N-GREET WITH THE ANIMAL CAN TAKE PLACE. animal.description:
Blu is big beautiful boy hoping for a home of his very own. At 70+ pounds and approx 3 years old, he is an ACTIVE dog + human friendly terrier. NO RENTERS PLEASE due to standard breed restrictions. Blu is a strong boy and fetch is his favorite. If you have a decent throw and a yard to run, Blu is your boy! 

Blu is being fostered in Georgetown MA and has proven himself the goofiest of dogs. He is learning all the basics, still loving fetch, and is best in a home with kids 12+ due to his size, no exceptions please. He can be adopted as a second dog or as an only dog too. He really loves his people and again, due to his size, needs dog-experienced folks that will continue with his foundation of training. Bully breed experience is preferred. He is currently living with another female working breed. 

Read through our adoption process and other adoption FAQs here www.rescueinc.dog/FAQs

All of our pups come with the following: 


	Spayed or Neutered
	Age appropriate vaccinations + dewormed + 4DX test (if older than 6 months)
	New martingale collar with 6' lead + temp ID tag
	30 days free insurance to be activated within 24 hours of your wellness visit with your veterinarian
	Microchip with free registration for your new pup, but also for any other pets in your household too!
	Southern pups, younger than 6 months, come with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm prevention to prevent any lapse of protection 
	Our southern dogs, 6 months and older, come with a **Proheart 6 injection which provides 6 months of Heartworm protection (approx value of $100) + dose of flea / tick preventative


**dogs surrendered to us in MA do not recieve the Proheart 6 injection but do go home with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm preventative so there is no lapse in protection

Ages listed can be approximate and breed mixes are a best guess based on physical characteristics. 

If you are seeing this listing on Petfinder, please apply through the link on our website at www.rescueinc.dog/adopt 

Please do not email with questions or message through Petfinder. Communication with the rescue always starts with submitting an application. 

If you see this listing, the pup is still available. We pull listings after 2 to 3 viable applications are submitted.

animal.description:
Lucky is a 4-5 year old 65 pound sharpei mix. If you can't tell by the scars on this boys poor face he's lived a very rough life. We suspect he was a bait dog judging by all the scars along his whole body and face. He flinched when touched and is a broken down boy. But he is slowly coming along. He has never shown any aggression whatsoever. He's just shut down and needs patience and love to teach him how to be a normal dog. He knows his routines and hasn't had an accident inside the house and isn't destructive when left alone. He is very dog friendly but still doesn't know exactly how to play but is very patient. Lucky deserves a loving home to finally feel safe. 
 

If you'd like to add Lucky to your family please apply at ruffhousedogs.org

animal.description:
Hi my names is Juno and I’m an 8 year old Boxer mix looking for my perfect home. My perfect home would have people who spend most of their time with me, maybe a small dog or older children (over 10), though I would prefer to be your only baby. I will need to be allowed on the couch and bed, this is non-negotiable. I am kennel trained and house broken. I come when you call, I can sit and am even getting better on my leash. I am sweet as can be but please expect me to take a little bit of time to get comfortable. When I do, expect some serious cuddling! If I choose you as my person, I will never leave your side! You will have lots of laughter in your life because I’m a bit of a klutz and I love to talk. If you meet my above requirements, contact my people!

Breed: Boxer/Pit Bull mix
Sex: Spayed Female
Age: 8 years
Size: 54 lbs
Arrival Date: 1-18-21

Juno is spayed, up to date on shots, heart worm tested negative and microchipped.

animal.description:
Flounder is young, active, go-getter. He likes being with people, being petted and played with. He loves to chase, catch, and shake plushy toys. Flounder seems to know Sit and Shake Paw already, and is working on other basic cues like Down. He'll benefit from positive reinforcement training to improve his leash walking skills as he tends to pull a little on leash (he is just so excited to explore!). He is currently a working to put a bit more weight on, but we don't think this will be a problem because he's very food motivated. Flounder was originally found as stray then taken to rural shelter. He has not had a chance to be in doggie playgroup yet, but he wagged his tail and seemed comfortable being in the presence of another dog during his behavior assessment. We do not have information as to whether he lived previously with cats or children or about how he did in the home (ie if housebroken, crate-trained, etc.).

To self-schedule an appointment to meet available dogs at CHA Animal Shelter, visit:

animal.description:
If you're looking for cuddles and constant tail wags in a loyal companion, Wesley is the dog for you! This handsome fella is a Lab/German Shepherd mix who weighs 46 lbs. He is approximately 2 years old, neutered, and heartworm positive on medication. He was adopted as a young 10 week old puppy in Houston but unfortunately his previous owners were careless and let him fend on the streets by himself. However, this did not take away from his sweet personality and calm demeanor. He bonds very quickly with humans who show him affection and is playful with other canines (he currently resides in a foster home with another 30 lbs small/medium female dog). He likes to be close to his human and knows how to sit nicely and give you his paw for some soft chews/treats. Wesley is a fast learner - he is house trained and has learned to wait by the door if he wants to be let out or go on a walk. He also isn't afraid to step up to any obstacles, quite literally, as he recently learned to conquer stairs :)


His favorite activities include looking out the window & scoping out the neighborhood and best of all, snuggling up next to you while watching TV or basically any chance he gets!

 

*Homeownership Required!

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Ace is a terrier mix, and barely a year old. He loves everyone and everything! Ace was hit by a car in Kentucky in September and one of his legs was put in a cast. In October he was transported to Heartland where it was determined his leg was shattered and the best thing to do was to amputate. He is gets around great but still needs to work on strengthening his good rear leg. Ace loves other dogs and tries to get everyone to play with him! Despite this, he would do best in a calmer household that doesnt include people continuously coming and going. In his foster home he encountered cats for the first time and is learning they dont necessarily want to play with him. He still tries to chase cars so he does need a home away from heavy traffic as well as a home without a lot of stairs.

All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations, heartworm tested negative (age 7 months and older) and microchipped. We do not ship or transport. A dog's adoption donation is $200. There is a $5 fee for credit/debit cards.

If you are interested in adopting one of our dogs, please fill out an online application here: www.heartlandsmallanimalrescue.org/canine-application.html

animal.description:
To apply to adopt, please go to www.adoptgoodkarma.com/adopting/ and fill out the online application.  

Macaroni is about 2 years older and 52 pounds. He is good with other dogs. Due to his energy level he would probably be best with older kids. He is neutered, up to date on vaccines and preventatives and heartworm negative. 

He is part of our foster to adopt program. The rescue will cover his getting vetted by our veterinarians during the foster period. If it is a love connection the foster gets first dibs to adopt. Please fill out an application if you are interested in fostering him. Typically the adoption fee is $380 but if you foster and decide to adopt we show our gratitude by providing a $50 discount plus his vetting.

Please do not send inquiries asking if animals are still available, if you see it online, that means it is.  We only post available animals.  In order to adopt one of our puppies or dogs, an application must be filled out prior to Being invited to meet the dog.

Please note that these animals in most cases are abandoned and therefore breeds and sizes are our best estimates based on years of experience.  Many times we do not know the parents, so we are guessing.  If you are looking for a specific breed or size maybe rescue is not for you, it is very possible you will adopt a puppy we say will be medium size and the pup may be smaller than estimated or may be larger than estimated.  We do our best but many times we are wrong so please beware of this before rescuing from us.

animal.description:
CROSS POST FOR OUR NC PARTNERS. WILL ONLY BE BROUGHT NORTH WITH SERIOUS APPLICATION

Heidi is 3 years old and 60 lbs. She is an adorable girl who loves people, taking walks, taking treats gently from your hand, and rolling in the grass. Turned out onto the streets of NC, she had become very evasive. She birthed a litter of pups and finally trusted people enough to help her and the pups. Since then she has learned to love the finer things in life inside a home. She still enjoys a yard to romp in and needs a fence at least 5 ft. tall just to make sure she doesn't get memories of her old walkabouts and take off on an adventure. With other dogs she has done fine but sometimes she is unsure of wanting to share things. For now she would be best as and only dog while she continues to adjust and accept that she is now safe.

If you feel that you could fully commit to this beautiful gal who needs a second chance, please go to our website www.rdrne.org to fill out an applicaton.

animal.description:
ADDIE is a sweet affectionate dog about one year old. She is playful with dogs and humans. A lovely gentle dog :-)

Her adoption fee includes her spaying, vaccines, deworming, microchip. She was born on a reservation we work with. She has a best friend Clancy for your consideration as well - they came into the rescue together. She still needs some basic and leash training.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description: Jenna aka a GEM! I'll be 2 in April, adopt me in plenty of time to celebrate my birthday with me!  I'm a 60lb lover of people and great with dogs., I'm very energetic and need an active family or person to play, hike and walk me. We could have a blast at the dog park and proud to say that ones mine over there, the cute red husky! I still need some leash work as I get excited to be out cuz I wasn't getting enough exercise where I lived. My mom was overwhelmed with a baby and 4 dogs and she didn't realize that along with lots of human love, Huskies need exercise. We also love to be part of a pack, we love to be inside with our humans snuggling, sleeping, and getting pampered feeling a family member. I'll make you feel special too! I became a backyard dog after my puppy stage unfortunately, and my mom said I didn't have accidents inside when I was younger. I'm excited this time to be an indoor dog and just go outside to play, run and potty. Like you, I have things I like and don't like, while I love my neck and sides of my face rubbed, I don't like my hind legs touched but I'm plenty affectionate,  just look at my smile, I melt hearts so watch out! I'm spayed, vaccinated,  chipped and ready to meet YOU! Will you be the lucky one?

Tessa is a sweet, affectionate girl who was adopted a year and half ago to a couple that loved her.  Unfortunately, her family died, and she was recently returned to the shelter - confused and anxious.

Tessa walks beautifully on a leash and ambles around the yard in a calm manner.  She prefers to be close to the humans in her life which makes her current predicament heart wrenching.  She is crate trained and has previously lived with cats and children.  She would be best suited living in a calm home, with older children and no other dogs.

Hopefully there is a home for this soulful girl who wants nothing more than to curl up next to you and be loved.  She will be a loyal and loving companion.

Due to Covid, the shelter has an appointment only policy.  We ask potential adopters to fill out an application, prior to a scheduled meeting.  The staff is very accommodating, and we welcome any inquiries.

animal.description:
FROM COOPERS COACHES:
We are excited to announce Cooper will be available for this years draft. Cooper is a 5-6 month old American Staffy blend that is currently a free agent looking to get his start with an amazing team willing to take in a Rookie. He has spent the last month in training camp with the Holthus team where he has picked up the basic skills needed to contribute to his next team. He may play hard but don't be fooled this kids a lover including his love for all things comfortable.  
He has requested to go to a team with an indoor arena and would not be successful at a team like Green Bay due to his aversion to cold weather. He has a real love for food and has not missed a meal while working on bulking up for his future linebacker roll.  With that being said he is also a food thief and will finish off others plates if they are not as speedy as him which has lead the team to encourage him to eat alone. 
Although he is very energetic when he is on the field he also has a very strict 9pm bed time. He is mostly trained to used the outdoor facilities but is known for the occasional accident if its too cold out.  Cooper enjoys walking the track and knows how to kennel up outside of practice time. He'll need a little refining but has a rare upside and can be a starter from day one.

My name is Hank. I'm a brown and white, male mixed breed dog, possibly Saint Bernard and Lab. I currently weigh 65 lbs. I was found in Livermore on 01/23/21. I have been vaccinated, and will be neutered and micro-chipped before going to my new home. I'm located in kennel A-1. Because I can get rambunctious and am still learning some manners, I would be best suited for an adult only home at this time. If you already have another dog at home, you'll need to bring them to the shelter for an introduction prior to adoption.

If you're interested in adopting me, please contact the East County Animal Shelter at 925-803-7040.
